CAVALIERS at BULLS | NBA PRESEASON FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | October 5, 2021

The Chicago Bulls ended the game on a 15-5 run to defeat the Cleveland Cavaliers, 131-95. The Bulls were led by the 25 PTS and 4 three-pointers and 3 REB from Zach LaVine, while DeMar DeRozan also added 13 PTS. The Cavaliers were led by Collin Sexton, who had 14 PTS and 2 STL and 2 three-pointers. Bulls improve to 1-0, while the Cavaliers fall to 0-1.
